# Cloud Agent workflow

Use this when the task is delegated from Poke, GitHub, Linear, or Cursor Cloud.

Required behavior:

- Start by reading root `AGENTS.md`, `100X/AGENTS.md`, `TASKS.md`, `CONTEXT_LOG.md`,
  `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, and `100X/docs/AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`.
- Read the Codex-planned `100X/tasks/<TASK_ID>.md` before implementation.
- If the task spec is missing or ambiguous, stop and request a local Codex planning update instead
  of inventing architecture.
- Commit only scoped changes.
- Use verifier and test-runner subagents before claiming completion on non-trivial work.
- Use security-auditor when changes touch auth, permissions, secrets, user data, APIs, or database
  access.
- Update per-task `100X/state/` and `100X/logs/` files when the task has a durable task spec.
- End with commands run, risks, next action, and a Poke-ready summary under 100 words.

Never rely on external services unless the task explicitly requires them and the environment is
configured.
